Official C++ documentation - Might be hard to follow and understand for beginners. Visit official C++ documentation. Write a lot of C++ programming code- The only way you can learn programming is by writing a lot of code. Read C++ code- Join Github's open-source projects and read other people's code.
C++ is a powerful general-purpose programming language. It can be used to develop operating systems, browsers, games, and so on. C++ supports different ways of programming like procedural, object-oriented, functional, and so on. This makes C++ powerful as well as flexible.

There are two ways for learning  :
1. Paperbacks(With Books)
2. Online

If you prefer paperbacks, then you can refer the following books :

    The C++ Programming language by Bjarne Stroustrup. One of the best book because the guy who invented CPP wrote this book as well - For Professionals.
    C++ Primer by S. B. Lippman, J. Lajoie, B. E. Moo. - For beginners.
    Accelerated C++: Practical Programming by example by Andrew Koenig - For Intermediate

